  "body": "Dear devs,\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.9.18-stable`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\nCommit hash : f5382591874220287de253bfc08b10afd5244927\r\n\r\nWhen I using personal_sendTransaction and send contract like bellow:\r\n```\r\ndata = '0xa9059cbb' + wallet_to.zfill(64) + value.zfill(64)\r\nparams = [{\r\n            'from': wallet_from,\r\n            'to': self.contract_address,\r\n            'data': data,\r\n            'gas': '0x11170'\r\n        }, geth.password]\r\nresponse = geth.request(\r\n                'personal_sendTransaction',\r\n                params,\r\n                rpc_id\r\n            )\r\n```\r\nthe SSTORE operation consumes 20000 gas cost. Like bellow link(Row 524):\r\nhttps://etherscan.io/vmtrace?txhash=0x692b449682c49b61fe57d51ec8f1e0da479592744e0837d0821588bd2b3dcf35#raw\r\n\r\nYou can compare it with other transfer call which use 5000 gas(Row 524):\r\nhttps://etherscan.io/vmtrace?txhash=0x7257fb6bb5bdafdb36ae2638eb11accb73ac4048231873fe38590b7527c20d9d\r\n\r\nHere is my question. How can I change personal_sendTransaction parameters to use 5000 gas instead of 20000? Is there any way to reduce this SSTORE.\r\n\r\nP.S.: I created the smart contract transfer call with web3 and it used 5000 gas too.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
